Here are both approaches for MAUI Shell navigation with `IQueryAttributable`:

**1. Register the route:**
```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate — simple string parameter:**
```csharp
// From ProductListPage or its ViewModel
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");
```

**3. Navigate — passing the full object:**
```csharp
var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }   // any object, not just strings
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", navParams);
```

**4. Receive data with `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:**
```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            string productId = idObj.ToString();
            // fetch product from service, etc.
        }

        // Approach 2: full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            ProductName = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
        }
    }
}
```

**5. Wire the ViewModel to the page:**
```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String query param | `Dictionary<string, object>` |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | interpolated URI `?key=val` | overload accepting `IDictionary` |
| **Types** | strings only | any object |
| **Deep-link safe** | ✅ yes | ❌ no (objects can't be serialized to a URI) |

Both approaches deliver data to the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method — Shell calls it automatically when the page's `BindingContext` implements `IQueryAttributable`.
